title: Chet's Dallas
text: We went to Chet’s for brunch and it was amazing! Jorge, our waiter provided exceptionally friendly service and the food was amazing.

title: Chet's Dallas
text:
On the suggestion of a local resident, I visited Chet's during the busy Eclipse weekend in Dallas, and I'm glad I did. I sat at the bar and had a refreshing beer while deciding on a meal option. I eventually chose a burger, which was extremely tasty, and the bar chips it's served with were fresh and excellent. Several seated close by seemed to being enjoying their meals as well, with one commenting how tasty my burger looked . . . and it did.
The service at the bar (which was not overly busy) was only average, bordering on weak.  There wasn't much I needed, but I've appreciated that opportunity to order another drink.  The process to complete payment was a bit slow, but I was not in a rush at all, so that's OK.  I like the look of the place, and I do easily recommend it to others who might be in the area. Perhaps the service situation was a fluke this day.

title: Chick-fil-A
text:
Chick-fil-A is simply the best! From the moment you take that first bite of their delicious chicken sandwich, you know you're in for a treat. The service is always friendly and efficient, and the food is consistently fresh and flavorful.

Whether you're craving their classic chicken sandwich, their crispy nuggets, or their mouthwatering waffle fries, Chick-fil-A never disappoints. Plus, their commitment to customer satisfaction shines through in every interaction.

It's not just a fast-food joint; it's a place where you feel welcomed and valued. Whether you're grabbing a quick meal on the go or enjoying a leisurely lunch with friends, Chick-fil-A is always a top choice. Five stars for the best chicken around!

title: Chick-fil-A

title: Chick-fil-A
text: One of my most disappointing experiences with Chick-fil-A occurred recently. Despite having placed numerous large catering orders at various locations in the past, I was shocked by the smaller size of my recent order and the multitude of issues it caused. I placed the order earlier in the day for pickup that evening on the 15th for a party. However, upon arriving at 7:45-7:50 for the 7:30 pickup window, my order was nowhere to be found. When I addressed the issue with the managers and team lead, I was met with a lack of care and attention. Overhearing the assistant general manager and a team lead speaking in Spanish (possibly assuming I didn't understand), I was dismayed to hear them dismiss the situation, claiming it wasn't a big deal because they hadn't seen my order. After waiting an additional 10 minutes, another team lead informed me that it would take another 15-20 minutes to thaw the bread for the sandwiches I ordered, or I could opt for wraps instead. Reluctantly, I agreed to change my order to expedite the process. Finally, an hour past the confirmed pickup time, I received my order, causing me to miss most of the party I was attending. All I received in return for this frustrating experience was an offer for a free milkshake or meal.

text: Update: Try their very good soup!! Be prepared to wait for your food. Not a quick lunch by any stretch. Allow extra time, or get there early. The soup was very thick, (like stew) and spicy so I added some beef broth I had a my office. Today I tried the chicken salad. Not as good as the beef Barbados I had last time. They still do not have a very mild option on salsa. All of the salsa choices were hot. Still Very busy and seating was hard to come by. title: Grill & Vine
text: We went to dinner at the Grill and Vine restaurant as a party of seven on April 8th. Five of the people were satisfied with their meal, but my daughter and I ordered the kale and quinoa salad, which was extremely sparse. It had virtually no quinoa, possibly one cut up apricot and one cut up cucumber and dressing that was advertised as curry, but tasted like pure oil. The kale was very hard and inedible. Each of us was charged $16 for our salads which amounted to $32. We were both extremely disappointed and upset but were hosting guests from out of town and did not want to complain or have to wait 20 minutes for new dinners if we ordered them. It was already a long wait to get our food originally. I am extremely upset and no one is getting back to me from management. My voicemail is sitting ignored. I offered to scan and send a copy of our receipt so they could give me a refund which be would be a small portion of what we spent  I am looking for a refund for those two salads .Wish me luck. By the way, the atmosphere was lovely and our server Alfredo was great. My advice: avoid the kale and quinoa salad like the plague.

title: Grill & Vine
text:
I visited Grill and Vine at the Westin Downtown Dallas and had one of the worst dining experiences of my life. The food and menu items were subpar, my server didn’t know in-depth about any items on the menu, but those things were not a big deal. When my check comes for $220, I give my card and the server comes back saying that only $160 was deducted and that I still owe the additional $60. So I check my account, things are all good so I give back my card to charge the rest. They then charge me an additional $180 and are saying I still owe more money. Seeing that I’ve already been charged $340 for a $220 bill I immediately go to the manager bc it makes no sense whatsoever. The manager proceeds to tell me that the card reader automatically charged the amount of $180 and he doesn’t know why. In what world does a card reader charge random amounts? You would have to type in the amount owed to be charged.

While trying to see what’s going on and get my money back, Louis Almassy comes over and immediately tells me to calm down, calls me aggressive, and threatens to call the authorities on me without even knowing what’s going on or why I’m upset about being overcharged. He continued to call me aggressive and threatened to call the cops on me all for being upset about money being taken from me. I didn’t appreciate being called names and being threatened with cops for simply just calling out being overcharged.

I truly believe that I was only threatened with the cops being called because I’m black as there was nothing happening that warranted a cop being involved when again, money was taken from ME. Louis saw a black man upset and immediately pegged me as the problem without even getting an understanding of the situation. Even after getting an understanding, he never apologized for threatening to call the cops.

Furthermore, Louis is a loss prevention manager which “protects a company's assets from fraud and theft”, why would I be reprimanded by him when I’m the one in need of help? This dining experience was by far the worst experience I’ve ever had.

title: Grill & Vine
text: I booked this venue for Valentine’s Day with my wife. $85 per person is reasonable so I booked it. We were greeted promptly and politely by the hostess. The restaurant was basically empty, which made me wonder why the booking time was so limited. It took a few minutes to be greeted and offered drinks, but the bar was busy so we understood. When we placed our order, we watched our drinks sit on the bar for 8 minutes before my wife got up and got them for us. When it came time to order from the fixed menu, I was concerned when they didn’t ask what temperature I wanted my filet. Come to find out, it’s only well done. They brought out my plate with mushrooms, some sort of potato, and a thin filet cooked WELL DONE. It was painfully obvious the steak was premade and microwaved to order. My wife got scallops and risotto, the scallops had a strong fishy smell to them, which is NOT in the norm. I sent my steak back to be prepared medium rare as a filet should be. The product they returned to me was BLUE RARE at best. At this point, I was annoyed. So I asked them to return the food and bring us our check. I gladly paid for my wife’s meal since she tolerated the scallops. The oxtail pie appetizer was bland, and the cappuccino tomato soup starter was good, but was maybe an ounce. To top it off, they brought h wife her dessert and sent back mine since I returned my meal, and requested it to be removed (I took one bite of my well done steak). While I understand they shouldn’t just hand stuff out, they should have at least made an effort to remedy the poor food quality. I don’t blame the server at all. Either way, I paid $113 for my wife’s meal that was mediocre at best. The risotto was bland and overcooked along with the overly fishy scallops. I hope management fixes this for future diners. Luckily, we found an Italian place down the street to eat.

title: Henry's Majestic
text:
Henry's Majestic: A Disaster From Start to Finish

Starving after Church, Service Left Us Praying for Salvation

We arrived at Henry's Majestic with high hopes after hearing good things, only to be met with a nightmare of a dining experience. Let's just say our Easter celebration went from holy to "holy moly, this place is bad!"

Reservations Don't Mean Reservations

Despite having a reservation, our party of ten (including restless kids) waited a soul-crushing **hour and a half** for our food. By the time it arrived, we were famished and past the point of polite conversation.

A Sticky Situation (Literally)

A quick trip to the men's room did little to improve our mood. The floor was a disgusting tribute to those who came before us, leaving a lingering question about the overall cleanliness of the establishment.

Food? More Like a Food Quest

The agonizing wait for our entrees wasn't the end of the saga. After finally getting our food, it took another **45 minutes** just to receive a measly dessert.  Apparently, patience is a key ingredient at Henry's Majestic, because you'll need it in biblical proportions.

The Kitchen Gods Said "No" to My Friend's Meal

One member of our party never even received their dinner! Two whole hours vanished, and poof, no food appeared. The waiter's excuse of a "busy Easter rush" was laughable considering we had reservations. Shouldn't they have been prepared for a holiday crowd?

The Service? Non-Existent

Our waiter, Sam, tried his best, but  it wasn't enough to salvage this disaster.  There were no apologies, no attempt to fix the situation, just an acceptance of defeat.

The Last Supper (We Wish!)

This experience left a worse taste in our mouths than last year's fruitcake. Henry's Majestic is a place we'll be avoiding like the plague.  Save yourself the frustration and your hard-earned cash – take your Easter celebration elsewhere.

text: Very disappointing experience at this restaurant. My family was visiting from out of town and heard good things about this place. We walked in after spending the morning at the Dallas aquarium. We ordered a burger, wedge salad, hot dog, and chicken sandwich. It took about an hour for all our food to come out and at three separate times. My son’s burger was brought out first (by mistake from another table’s order) and our server ended up saying he could keep it and our food would be out shortly. About 20 minutes later by the time my son was finished my salad arrived. We were still missing my husband and daughter’s food. I went ahead and ate my salad and when I was finishing my lunch the rest of the food arrived. This was about 45 minutes after our order had been placed and the restaurant was not busy by any means. The hot dog had mustard on it which we had told the server to omit when we placed our order. When asked if we could get a new hot dog with just ketchup as originally ordered and keep the fries (our daughter was so hungry at this point) the server seemed annoyed. She brought us a new hot dog within a few minutes…drowning in ketchup, about 3 times the amount that was on the original hot dog, looking sloppy and gross overall. They were clearly annoyed we had requested a new one. This place has a fun overall bar atmosphere and an area for a live band. Maybe for a night out drinking it’s great but for a family meal they totally missed the mark.

title: Pizza Hut
text:
By far my worst experience with any pizza hut. We accepted the 1 hour wait time. When the delivery guy (later identified as a PH worker vs door dash per the store worker after calling back) came, we were given 2 boxes and a wings container. One pizza box was entirely EMPTY! Who in their right mind seals an empty box and then also doesn't notice how EMPTY it feels?

After calling back. The worker offered to either get a redelivery (an extra hour wait 😤) or store credit. The 1 star given was for the store worker who offered a credit in an amount more than the product that we ordered, which is fair due to the inconvenience and hunger my family endured after not receiving the amount of food we prepared for. Thank you store worker for making it a bit better and for apologizing on behalf of the business.
I'll have to go in person to use my credit next time however that will likely be the last time I'll give my business to that specific franchise.

title: Taqueria El Chilango
text:
This real mexican restaurant has changed its name to Martinez taqueria.
By real mexican restaurant I mean traditional cuisine. It tasted like my grandmother was cooking.
I mentioned to my wife that I felt like having huitlacoche(a mushroom that is harvested from corn) she asked at her work and someone mentioned the restaurant by it's former name.
I had a gordita with chicharrón en salsa verde while waiting for my huitlacoche quesadilla. The gordita was light tasting with a slight crunch  but filled with chicharrón and cotija cheese. The huitlacoche quesadilla was HUGE about 20 inches long filled with cotija cheese, chopped onions and of course tons of huitlacoche. Table side they have salsa roja and salsa verde. I WILL RETURN TO SAMPLE THE REST OF THE MENU!

text: Amazing restaurant and incredible food. We first stopped here because we were working in the area and it was lunch and it caught my eye. The Half Chicken is out of this world its so good, after one trip it became the benchmark for chicken I get from anywhere I go. It's always 'this chicken is good, but it's not as good as Pollo Regio.' I am grateful to Emma and Angie because they make it a wonderful experience when we come by, and we have come by 3 or 4 times a week when we are working in town because the food is that good and the atmosphere is so inviting. The Half Chicken is amazing, but everything else is great too, and it all pairs amazing with their chips and the Verde salsa! Thanks so much to everyone here on the Pollo Regio team.

title: Seafood City Restaurant
text: I was very hesitant to try this place because of the bad reviews I saw; at the same time I want to try it for myself and see for myself. First impression: a very old & dirty fried chicken restaurant, a step down from Lisa’s Chicken. The price is relatively fair, quite competitive to other fried chicken places. I was able to get a 3pc chicken dinner (2 sides) and a “medium” drink for under $10. The chicken tasted very bland, very greasy and left a bad after taste. I believe they’ve used rotten chicken to fry, very gross, and don’t even get me started with their soggy fries I couldn’t even finish. The drink is not up to its size. I got the medium one ($1.59) and it is very clearly not 24 oz as advertised. It is more like 16 oz. They fill it up with ice so you don’t get the full volume of drink, and they would charge you 50 cents for refill. Because of how this restaurant offers dirt poor quality of food, I was going to give it a 1-star review. However, an extra star rating was given by me because they let me get the refill for free. Not a place to return.

text:

Got home and we discovered that the "chicken" did not make it into the container!!! I've had multiple mishaps (about 60%) from this location ranging from missing sandwiches, missing GF buns, and missing items - most of these I've actually let go. They do get it right sometimes and I do what I can to check the order to prevent it at the counter.

However, to have to open individual containers to make sure the chicken was there is going too bit much babysitting. We should expect a certain amount of quality. And the place wasn't even that busy today... The drive thru wasn't long and the dining area was not full.

It's hard to stay away from this location since it's the only one on the way but the service becomes a bit too much.
